Vim Files to enable syntax highlighting for Gromacs files.

Works with  mdp, ndx and top files.

=============
Installation:
=============

  Normal Way
  ~~~~~~~~~~
Go to your ~/.vim directory

If "syntax" and "ftdetect" directories don't exist, copy them from github.
If they are, copy only files inside. Otherwise, existing files will be replaced.

  VimBall Way (Vim >= 7.0)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Download the vimball "gromacs.vba"
Open it with vi and type:
  - :so %
  - :q!

